Each VPC bare metal server has two 100Gbits/s network interfaces connected to the physical network providing a total 100Gbits/s bandwidth.
A PCI interface (NIC) provides an abstraction of a physical interface and you can have up to 8 PCI NICs per host. In VCF deployments, two PCI interfaces are used as vSwitch uplinks.
